{"article_id":"nsLbhkbAIMkfvU8K","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Obama 's Call For Higher Minimum Wage Could Have Ripple Effect","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"After more than five years of recession and painfully slow recovery ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"President Obama has sent a powerful signal","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that he thinks","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"the U.S. economy is now in much better shape","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"good enough , at least ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"to provide workers with raises .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"In his State of the Union address Tuesday night , Obama called upon Congress to boost the federal minimum wage to $ 9 an hour by 2015 , up from the current $ 7.25 .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"The wage would rise in steps ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"and","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"after hitting the maximum in two years ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"would thereafter be indexed to inflation .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"In the president 's first term , the unemployment rate was very high ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"peaking at 10 percent in October 2009 .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"And during those four years , Obama never seriously pushed Congress for legislation","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"to force employers to pay more .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Tuesday night , he changed direction ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"saying in his State of the Union speech","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that he wants Congress to drive up wages for millions of workers","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"by forcing up the benchmark minimum wage .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Even though only a relatively small percentage of workers make $ 7.25 an hour ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that pay level serves as a wage floor for all workers .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"When it moves higher ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"other wages ratchet up too .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"In other words ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"if Congress were to boost the minimum hourly wage ,","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"then a person","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"currently making $ 9","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"likely could move up to $ 10 or even $ 11 an hour","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"as employers adjusted pay scales to higher levels","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"to compete for the better low-wage workers .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"The White House says","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"15 million workers would benefit directly from a higher minimum wage ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"but many economists say","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"that millions more would gain too","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"after taking into account the ripple effect","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"as the whole wage scale moves up .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"`` We know","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"our economy is stronger","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"when we reward an honest day 's work with honest wages , ''","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Obama said .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"`` But today , a full-time worker","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"making the minimum wage","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"earns $ 14,500 a year . ''","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that 's not enough money","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"to keep a family above the poverty line .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"`` Let 's declare","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that in the wealthiest nation on Earth , no one","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"who works full time","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"should have to live in poverty ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"and raise the federal minimum wage to $ 9 an hour .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"This single step would raise the incomes of millions of working families . ''","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"The president 's focus on the minimum wage came as something of a surprise , even to longtime supporters of a pay increase .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Sen. Amy Klobuchar , D-Minn. , said in an interview Wednesday morning","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"while she agrees with the president ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"`` I did n't know","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"he would bring it up . ''","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"Given that the wage push was unexpected ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"she said","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"she did not know","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"how Democratic lawmakers might put together their strategy","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"for getting the legislation passed .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"For many years , it had been Massachusetts Democratic Sen. Edward Kennedy","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"who led congressional battles for higher wages .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"But with his death in August 2009","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"- one month after the last minimum wage hike took effect -","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"supporters will need a new champion in Congress","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"to marshal the troops .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Opponents already are gearing up for the fight .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"At a press conference this morning , House Speaker John Boehner , a Republican , made it clear","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"he would work against minimum-wage legislation .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"`` When you raise the price of employment ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"guess what happens ?","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"You get less of it , ''","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"Boehner said .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"`` At a time","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"when the American people are still asking the question ,","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"'Where are the jobs ? '","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"why would we want to make it harder for small employers to hire people ? ''","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"Congress last passed a bill","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"establishing a series of minimum wage increases in 2007","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"before the Great Recession began .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"The last of those increases took the pay up to $ 7.25 ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"where it has remained frozen .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Nineteen states plus the District of Columbia have minimum wages above $ 7.25 .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"For example , in Washington state , the pay is now up to $ 9.19 an hour","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"- the highest minimum in the country .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"If the federal level were to rise ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"many of those 19 states would most likely pass new legislation","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"to exceed it .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"If the past is any indicator ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"business groups","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"- particularly the National Restaurant Association -","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"will put up a fierce fight","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"to block any federal minimum wage increase .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Another group","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"backed by the restaurant and hotel industries","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"says","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"an increase in the minimum wage can hurt the economy .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"`` The President 's minimum wage hike ignores both simple economic logic as well as the overwhelming scholarly consensus on minimum wage hikes , ''","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Michael Saltsman , research director of the Employment Policies Institute , said in a statement .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"The institute says","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"research `` points to a loss of job opportunities","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"following a minimum wage hike . ''","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"But many economists point to studies","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"that show","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"a higher minimum wage does little to hurt job creation .","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Instead , these economists argue","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"that a higher wage reduces income inequality","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"and puts more money into the hands of the consumers","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"who can spend it .","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"So ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"the argument goes ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"while a pizza-shop owner might have to spend more on his payroll under new wage legislation ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"he also would see a boost in revenues","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"as customers find themselves enjoying bigger paydays .","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"The minimum wage has been a hot-button issue with business groups since its introduction in 1938 .","depth":4},{"id":121,"text":"They argue","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"that a federal minimum wage is inflationary","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"and represents an unnecessary government intervention in the labor market .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"They say","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"labor supply and demand alone should set wages , not lawmakers .","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"Supporters disagree .","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"They say","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"inflation is very low ,","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"while income inequality is growing .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"Working people lack of spending power ,","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"and that 's what is inhibiting economic growth ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"the argument goes .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"`` We applaud the president","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"for expressing support","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"for raising the minimum wage","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"and tying it to the cost of living , ''","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Richard Trumka , president of the AFL-CIO , said in a statement on behalf of the labor organization .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"the economy is not suffering from high wages","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"but rather from `` wage stagnation and growing inequality . ''","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"Between 2000 and 2010 , U.S. median income fell 7 percent","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"after adjusting for inflation ,","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"according to census data .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"Over the past year , the unemployment rate has hovered at or just below 8 percent .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":289,"left":0,"right":288,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":288,"left":263,"right":287,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":156,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":151,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":1,"right":150,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":2,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":3,"right":148,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":4,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":5,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":8,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":9,"right":153,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":10,"right":152,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":262,"left":207,"right":261,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":180,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":163,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":159,"right":162,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":157,"right":158,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p